[This sounds like a few cows at these dairies may have tested positive for tuberculosis. Because bovine TB is such a slow insidious disease, it is difficult to detect. In the USA, such a situation would result in a depopulation of the herd due to the nature of the disease. This is especially true in trying to eliminate the disease. Elimination of the disease is especially important to the country purchasing the animals or the meat.

The state of Guerrero, Mexico, may be found on the interactive healthmap at: http://healthmap.org/r/3aGn. - Mod.TG]
